{"identifier": "cs_email10:4cadc33e", "prompt_str": "<TO_OPTIMIZE kind="User">
Review this email and determine its core technical focus. Route it to exactly one person based on these scopes:

ankush - Data Systems:
• Core focus: Raw data operations, exports, processing pipelines
• Scope: Database queries, ETL jobs, data modeling
• Note: Handles data mechanics, not business reporting

ben - Financial Systems:
• Core focus: Payment processing and billing operations  
• Scope: Transaction handling, invoicing, pricing engines
• Note: Technical payment issues, not business decisions

jerry - Interface Systems:
• Core focus: User interaction and display logic
• Scope: Visual layout, UI components, display formatting
• Note: How things look/work, not backend performance

julia - Education Systems:
• Core focus: Learning platform operations
• Scope: Course delivery, scheduling mechanics, student tracking
• Note: Platform functionality, not content creation

miles - Access Systems:
• Core focus: Permission management and configuration
• Scope: Role definitions, access control, system settings
• Note: How permissions work, not security mechanisms

nuno - Security Systems:
• Core focus: Authentication and security controls
• Scope: Login systems, 2FA, security policies
• Note: Security mechanisms, not user permissions

sarah - Integration Systems:
• Core focus: External system connections
• Scope: APIs, webhooks, deployment environments
• Note: How systems connect, not individual features

tom - Performance Systems:
• Core focus: System behavior and reliability
• Scope: Speed issues, error handling, system stability
• Note: How well things work, not how they look

will - Analytics Systems:
• Core focus: Business intelligence and reporting
• Scope: Dashboards, metrics, trend analysis
• Note: Analyzing data, not raw data operations

Review this email and determine its core technical focus. Route it to exactly one person based on these scopes:

ankush - Data Systems:
• Core focus: Raw data operations, exports, processing pipelines
• Scope: Database queries, ETL jobs, data modeling
• Note: Handles data mechanics, not business reporting

ben - Financial Systems:
• Core focus: Payment processing and billing operations  
• Scope: Transaction handling, invoicing, pricing engines
• Note: Technical payment issues, not business decisions

jerry - Interface Systems:
• Core focus: User interaction and display logic
• Scope: Visual layout, UI components, display formatting
• Note: How things look/work, not backend performance

julia - Education Systems:
• Core focus: Learning platform operations
• Scope: Course delivery, scheduling mechanics, student tracking
• Note: Platform functionality, not content creation

miles - Access Systems:
• Core focus: Permission management and configuration
• Scope: Role definitions, access control, system settings
• Note: How permissions work, not security mechanisms

nuno - Security Systems:
• Core focus: Authentication and security controls
• Scope: Login systems, 2FA, security policies
• Note: Security mechanisms, not user permissions

sarah - Integration Systems:
• Core focus: External system connections
• Scope: APIs, webhooks, deployment environments
• Note: How systems connect, not individual features

tom - Performance Systems:
• Core focus: System behavior and reliability
• Scope: Speed issues, error handling, system stability
• Note: How well things work, not how they look

will - Analytics Systems:
• Core focus: Business intelligence and reporting
• Scope: Dashboards, metrics, trend analysis
• Note: Analyzing data, not raw data operations
